<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1864,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1864,1890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<collectionCode box="[287,338,1864,1890]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/iskk-kcgq" name="Institute of Vertebrate Biology, The Czech Academy of Sciences" pageId="3" pageNumber="40">IVB</collectionCode>
length up to 
<number box="[493,530,1864,1890]" pageId="3" pageNumber="40" value="4.5">4.5</number>
times as long as width of eye stalk in the middle. Thorax pollinose on posterior part, scutellar spines up to 
<number box="[518,554,1904,1930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="40" value="3.5">3.5</number>
times as long as length of scutellum. Epandrium in dorsal view as wide as hypandrium. Only few hairs (
<number box="[503,549,1944,1970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="40" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
) at the base of hypandrium. Hypandrial bridge broad, slightly narrowed at the middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
